body:
Hello, when i updated to the latest version of react everything was wonderful but I started to notice something really important... Sometime the components that i created weren't there... so I started to debug my code and I found i made an exception inside the render function, something like 

This is an stupid example but it only to show an example...

```
var object1 = undefined;
console.log(object1.name);
```

So i never saw that error on the console... I just don't see anything...

This error was making me crazy... so i stated to debug React code and i found something and i don't know if its a bug or i need to solve it in a different way...

inside react.js

```
_renderValidatedComponent: function(childContext) {
    var renderedComponent;
    var previousContext = ReactContext.current;
    ReactContext.current = this._mergeChildContext(
      this._currentElement._context,
      childContext
    );
    ReactCurrentOwner.current = this;
    try {
      renderedComponent =
        this._renderValidatedComponentWithoutOwnerOrContext();
    }
    finally {
      ReactContext.current = previousContext;
      ReactCurrentOwner.current = null;
    }
```

here we can see the "try" haven't got a "catch"... after i added the "catch" the console started to show the errors inside my render function...

```
_renderValidatedComponent: function(childContext) {
    var renderedComponent;
    var previousContext = ReactContext.current;
    ReactContext.current = this._mergeChildContext(
      this._currentElement._context,
      childContext
    );
    ReactCurrentOwner.current = this;
    try {
      renderedComponent =
        this._renderValidatedComponentWithoutOwnerOrContext();
    }
    catch (ex) {
      console.error(ex);
    }
    finally {
      ReactContext.current = previousContext;
      ReactCurrentOwner.current = null;
    }
```

I hope this is ok and its not my mistake...

Thanks!
